<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F3EFEB048A7556CFC9AFB69" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F3EFEB048A7556CFC1FFB85" blockId="368.[151,1436,576,1430]" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F3EFEB048A7556CFE06FDA9" bold="true" box="[151,419,576,601]" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F3EFEB04A41556DFD5EFDA9" box="[625,763,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" unit="mm" value="3.2" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="2.8">2.8–3.6 mm</quantity>
. Usually testaceous-ferruginous, with petiole black; antenna usually testaceous, with segments 9–10 whitish (occasionally antennal segment 9 partly whitish). In specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F3EFEB048A755A6FEA3FD52" box="[151,262,650,674]" name="Myanmar" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868F3EFEB0492255A5FE21FD51" box="[274,388,649,673]" degrees="17" direction="north" minutes="38.9" orientation="latitude" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" precision="92" value="17.648333">17°38.9'N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868F3EFEB049BD55A5FE5BFD51" box="[397,510,649,673]" degrees="94" direction="east" minutes="38.1" orientation="longitude" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" precision="92" value="94.635">94°38.1'E</geoCoordinate>
, antenna testaceous-brown, except segments 1 and 10 whitish. In specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F3EFEB048A75581FF78FD35" box="[151,221,685,709]" name="China" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">China</collectingCountry>
, Mt. Jinggangshan, antenna brown, except rhinaria areas testaceous, and mesosoma brown-testaceous. Antenna clavate; antennal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38F3EFEB04A6D55FDFD1AFD19" box="[605,703,721,745]" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">holotype</typeStatus>
in following proportions: 16:13:38:23:18:12:12:13:12:20. Head very excavated, shiny, smooth, unsculptured, hairless; frontal line complete; occipital carina absent; POL = 0.3; OL = 2; OOL = 8.5. Palpal formula 3/2 or 4/2. Pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression, shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Scutum shiny, unsculptured, laterally without pointed apophyses. Scutellum shiny, smooth, flat, without lateral pointed apophyses. Metanotum shiny, unsculptured, not hollow behind scutellum, with sides protruding; lateral protrusions pointed (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F3EFEB04A5B54A9FD49FC6D" box="[619,748,901,925]" captionStart="PLATE 113" captionStartId="367.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[235,1404,216,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-103@367.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="367" captionText="PLATE 113. A, C, E. Scutum + metathorax + propodeum. G. Mesosoma. B, D, F, H. Chelae. A, B. Gonatopus lankae, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C, D. G.malesiae, female (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. muiri, holotype (from Olmi 1984). G, H. G. nepalensis, holotype (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.63 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B and D, 0.59 mm for C, 0.61 mm for E, 0.21 mm for F, 0.75 mm for G and 0.25 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278772/files/figure.png" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Plate 113C</figureCitation>
). Metathorax + propodeum shiny, hairless, with disc and anterior surface unsculptured; disc of metathorax + propodeum without median longitudinal furrow; posterior surface of propodeum transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture very slightly distinct. In specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F3EFEB048A754DEFEA3FBFA" box="[151,262,1010,1034]" name="Myanmar" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868F3EFEB0492754DDFE2DFBF9" box="[279,392,1009,1033]" degrees="17" direction="north" minutes="38.9" orientation="latitude" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" precision="92" value="17.648333">17°38.9'N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868F3EFEB049A654DDFDA2FBF9" box="[406,519,1009,1033]" degrees="94" direction="east" minutes="38.1" orientation="longitude" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" precision="92" value="94.635">94°38.1'E</geoCoordinate>
, meso-metapleural suture partly and slightly visible (not visible on sides of metanotum). Segment 1 of protarsus usually shorter than segment 4 (13:16). Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F3EFEB04C9C5339FA8CFBDD" box="[1196,1321,1045,1069]" captionStart="PLATE 113" captionStartId="367.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[235,1404,216,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-103@367.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="367" captionText="PLATE 113. A, C, E. Scutum + metathorax + propodeum. G. Mesosoma. B, D, F, H. Chelae. A, B. Gonatopus lankae, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C, D. G.malesiae, female (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. muiri, holotype (from Olmi 1984). G, H. G. nepalensis, holotype (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.63 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B and D, 0.59 mm for C, 0.61 mm for E, 0.21 mm for F, 0.75 mm for G and 0.25 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278772/files/figure.png" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Plate 113D</figureCitation>
) with one large subapical tooth and one row of seven–ten lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F3EFEB04C775315FB63FBA1" box="[1095,1222,1081,1105]" captionStart="PLATE 113" captionStartId="367.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[235,1404,216,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-103@367.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="367" captionText="PLATE 113. A, C, E. Scutum + metathorax + propodeum. G. Mesosoma. B, D, F, H. Chelae. A, B. Gonatopus lankae, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C, D. G.malesiae, female (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. muiri, holotype (from Olmi 1984). G, H. G. nepalensis, holotype (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.63 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B and D, 0.59 mm for C, 0.61 mm for E, 0.21 mm for F, 0.75 mm for G and 0.25 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278772/files/figure.png" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Plate 113D</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 12–17 lamellae; distal apex with at least 15 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F3EFEB048F753ADFC9AFB69" blockId="368.[151,1436,576,1430]" box="[199,831,1153,1177]" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F3EFEB048F753ADFEAEFB69" bold="true" box="[199,267,1153,1177]" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown (see 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F3EFEB049F253ADFC9EFB69" authority="(Olmi))" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[450,827,1153,1177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gonatopus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sarawakensis">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F3EFEB049F253ADFD7EFB69" box="[450,731,1153,1177]" italics="true" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Gonatopus sarawakensis</emphasis>
(Olmi))
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
